## Database Schema (proposed)

### `products`
| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | uuid PK | |
| `slug` | text unique | URL slug |
| `name` | text | |
| `tagline` | text | One-liner shown on card |
| `description` | text | Long form, supports MDX |
| `category` | text | e.g. `automation`, `vision`, `agent`, `data` |
| `status` | text | `live` / `beta` / `concept` |
| `cover_image` | text | Path under /public/products |
| `order` | int | Display order in gallery |
| `created_at` | timestamptz | |

### `leads`
| Column | Type | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `id` | uuid PK | |
| `name` | text | |
| `email` | text | |
| `company` | text nullable | |
| `message` | text | |
| `source` | text | `contact-form` / `book-call` / `product:<slug>` |
| `created_at` | timestamptz | |

> Skip the DB entirely if we go MDX-only for products and pipe leads straight to email.

