## Coding Standards

### Do
- TypeScript strict mode on
- Server-only secrets stay server-only (never `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` for keys)
- Validate every API input with Zod
- One component = one responsibility
- Tailwind utility-first; extract to component when used 3+ times
- All forms have `loading`, `error`, and `success` states

### Don't
- Don't import reference-site assets, fonts via their CDN, or copy their copy
- Don't store secrets in client components
- Don't hardcode product data in components — read from MDX/DB
- Don't commit `.env.local`, `node_modules`, `.next`, `.tmp/`

